==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ossicle
<hw>Os"si*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ossiculum</ets>, dim. of <ets>os</ets>, <ets>ossis</ets>, a
bone.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A little bone; <as>as, the auditory
<ex>ossicles</ex> in the tympanum of the ear</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of numerous small calcareous
structures forming the skeleton of certain echinoderms, as the
starfishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ossicular</ent>⟦br⟧
